          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex> be as in (IV) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5" href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.xml" number="5.3.5" />.
    We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:em>proper <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>-truncated hypercover</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> if the arrows in <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.1" href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="5.3.5.1" /> are proper and surjective.
    For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k=\infty ]]></fr:tex>, we simply say "proper hypercover".</fr:p>
